  "faq": {
    "sectionLabel": "Questions",
    "title": "Everything you'd ask before signing up.",
    "subtitle": "Still curious? Our team replies to every message within one business day.",
    "contactUs": "Contact us",
    "q1": "Is Dossiat an employer, bank, or legal representative?",
    "a1": "No. Dossiat is a software provider — full stop. Our Terms of Service explicitly state that we are not an employer, financial institution, or legal representative. All liability sits with the Agents and their clients. We provide the workflow, traceability, and communication tools; nothing more.",
    "q2": "How does the platform get paid on cash missions?",
    "a2": "Agents maintain a Platform Credit Balance. For a $100 cash mission with a 1% fee, we deduct $2 from that balance. Agents can top up credits anytime, or settle via a monthly consolidated invoice — whichever matches their cash flow.",
    "q3": "What happens if a dispute arises?",
    "a3": "The mission enters \"Reconciliation Mode\" — a structured chat room where both parties state their case and propose a solution. The goal is peer-to-peer, out-of-court resolution. We provide the audit trail, but we do not arbitrate, judge, or absorb liability. Professional and Enterprise plans get priority access to mediation.",
    "q4": "Which currencies are supported?",
    "a4": "USD, EUR, GBP, MAD, AED, SAR, CAD, AUD, JPY, CHF, and 30+ more. Each Agent selects their operating currency; the platform fee (1% with a $1 minimum) is calculated dynamically in that currency.",
    "q5": "Can my company connect Dossiat to our ERP?",
    "a5": "Yes — on the Enterprise tier. You get a dedicated REST API and webhook system to create missions, fetch expense data, and push reconciliation events directly into your internal tools."
  },
